tants in which every amino acid of the active site\n(except for the catalytically active residues E78 and E172) was mutated to\nevery other amino acid. Based on results from the single mutants we construct a\nset of 111 double mutants consisting of all possible pairs of single mutants\nwith the lowest barrier for a particular position and compute their reaction\nprofile. None of the mutants have, to our knowledge, been prepared\nexperimentally[...].\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 26 May 2013 18:46:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-09-16"}
